                "cooked": "<p>Hi AWOL - modern days soundcards are able to digitize at 96kHz and higher even, and some PC-soundcard oscilloscope software is taken advantage of this. Have a look at <a href=\"http://lare-india.blogspot.com/2010/06/rc-5-protocol-infrared.html\" class=\"inline-onebox\">RC-5 Protocol (InfraRed)</a>, specifically this image here</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://europe1.discourse-cdn.com/arduino/original/4X/0/7/e/07e47a88c45734905d3726b974dcb6110ecbbf37.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/17OR2HA6pm6rxIKdrP1IBF6cE63.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://europe1.discourse-cdn.com/arduino/original/4X/0/7/e/07e47a88c45734905d3726b974dcb6110ecbbf37.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"17OR2HA6pm6rxIKdrP1IBF6cE63\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"690\" height=\"487\" data-dominant-color=\"676768\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">720×509 87.1 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<p>for an example.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>cpixip</li>\n</ul>",
